{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1173,"text":"I wanted to talk to you today\nabout creative confidence."},{"time":5443,"text":"I'm going to start way back\nin the third grade"},{"time":8611,"text":"at Oakdale School in Barberton, Ohio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11997,"text":"I remember one day my best friend\nBrian was working on a project."},{"time":16490,"text":"He was making a horse out of the clay\nour teacher kept under the sink."},{"time":22116,"text":"And at one point, one of the girls\nthat was sitting at his table,"},{"time":25699,"text":"seeing what he was doing,\nleaned over and said to him,"},{"time":29337,"text":"\"That's terrible. That doesn't look\nanything like a horse.\""},{"time":33765,"text":"And Brian's shoulders sank."},{"time":35567,"text":"And he wadded up the clay horse\nand he threw it back in the bin."},{"time":39785,"text":"I never saw Brian do a project\nlike that ever again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44695,"text":"And I wonder how often\nthat happens, you know?"},{"time":48096,"text":"It seems like when I tell\nthat story of Brian to my class,"},{"time":53026,"text":"a lot of them want to come up after class"},{"time":55073,"text":"and tell me about\ntheir similar experience,"},{"time":57114,"text":"how a teacher shut them down,"},{"time":58748,"text":"or how a student\nwas particularly cruel to them."},{"time":61433,"text":"And then some kind of opt out\nof thinking of themselves as creative"},{"time":64999,"text":"at that point."},{"time":67155,"text":"And I see that opting out\nthat happens in childhood,"},{"time":70801,"text":"and it moves in and becomes\nmore ingrained, even,"},{"time":74120,"text":"by the time you get to adult life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78141,"text":"So we see a lot of this."},{"time":82302,"text":"When we have a workshop"},{"time":83726,"text":"or when we have clients\nin to work with us side by side,"},{"time":86496,"text":"eventually we get\nto the point in the process"},{"time":88797,"text":"that's kind of fuzzy or unconventional."},{"time":91743,"text":"And eventually, these big-shot executives\nwhip out their BlackBerrys"},{"time":95947,"text":"and they say they have to make\nreally important phone calls,"},{"time":98874,"text":"and they head for the exits."},{"time":101018,"text":"And they're just so uncomfortable."},{"time":103290,"text":"When we track them down\nand ask them what's going on,"},{"time":105933,"text":"they say something like,\n\"I'm just not the creative type.\""},{"time":109568,"text":"But we know that's not true."},{"time":111703,"text":"If they stick with the process,\nif they stick with it,"},{"time":114395,"text":"they end up doing amazing things."},{"time":116640,"text":"And they surprise themselves\nat just how innovative"},{"time":119614,"text":"they and their teams really are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123108,"text":"So I've been looking\nat this fear of judgment that we have,"},{"time":127718,"text":"that you don't do things, you're afraid\nyou're going to be judged;"},{"time":131224,"text":"if you don't say the right creative thing,\nyou're going to be judged."},{"time":135754,"text":"And I had a major breakthrough,"},{"time":137740,"text":"when I met the psychologist\nAlbert Bandura."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141931,"text":"I don't know if you know Albert Bandura,\nbut if you go to Wikipedia,"},{"time":145232,"text":"it says that he's the fourth most\nimportant psychologist in history --"},{"time":149398,"text":"you know, like Freud, Skinner,\nsomebody and Bandura."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153131,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154567,"text":"Bandura is 86 and he still\nworks at Stanford."},{"time":157575,"text":"And he's just a lovely guy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161082,"text":"So I went to see him,"},{"time":162386,"text":"because he's just worked\non phobias for a long time,"},{"time":165912,"text":"which I'm very interested in."},{"time":167369,"text":"He had developed this way,"},{"time":171631,"text":"this, kind of, methodology,"},{"time":174381,"text":"that ended up curing people\nin a very short amount of time,"},{"time":177356,"text":"like, in four hours."},{"time":178739,"text":"He had a huge cure rate\nof people who had phobias."},{"time":182199,"text":"And we talked about snakes\n-- I don't know why --"},{"time":185187,"text":"we talked about snakes\nand fear of snakes as a phobia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190271,"text":"And it was really enjoyable,\nreally interesting."},{"time":193251,"text":"He told me that he'd invite\nthe test subject in,"},{"time":198218,"text":"and he'd say, \"You know,\nthere's a snake in the next room"},{"time":201129,"text":"and we're going to go in there.\""},{"time":204421,"text":"To which, he reported,\nmost of them replied,"},{"time":206585,"text":"\"Hell no! I'm not going in there,\ncertainly if there's a snake in there.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":211389,"text":"But Bandura has a step-by-step\nprocess that was super successful."},{"time":215713,"text":"So he'd take people to this two-way mirror"},{"time":218643,"text":"looking into the room where the snake was."},{"time":221368,"text":"And he'd get them comfortable with that."},{"time":223432,"text":"Then through a series of steps,"},{"time":225012,"text":"he'd move them and they'd be standing\nin the doorway with the door open,"},{"time":228721,"text":"and they'd be looking in there."},{"time":230259,"text":"And he'd get them comfortable with that."},{"time":232230,"text":"And then many more steps\nlater, baby steps,"},{"time":234944,"text":"they'd be in the room, they'd have\na leather glove like a welder's glove on,"},{"time":239040,"text":"and they'd eventually touch the snake."},{"time":242575,"text":"And when they touched the snake,\neverything was fine. They were cured."},{"time":247203,"text":"In fact, everything was better than fine."},{"time":249347,"text":"These people who had\nlifelong fears of snakes"},{"time":253219,"text":"were saying things like,"},{"time":255396,"text":"\"Look how beautiful that snake is.\""},{"time":257398,"text":"And they were holding it in their laps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261673,"text":"Bandura calls this process\n\"guided mastery.\""},{"time":265582,"text":"I love that term: guided mastery."},{"time":269081,"text":"And something else happened."},{"time":271222,"text":"These people who went through the process\nand touched the snake"},{"time":274748,"text":"ended up having less anxiety\nabout other things in their lives."},{"time":279519,"text":"They tried harder, they persevered longer,"},{"time":282115,"text":"and they were more resilient\nin the face of failure."},{"time":285828,"text":"They just gained a new confidence."},{"time":290139,"text":"And Bandura calls\nthat confidence \"self-efficacy,\""},{"time":294599,"text":"the sense that you can change the world"},{"time":297511,"text":"and that you can attain\nwhat you set out to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301457,"text":"Well, meeting Bandura\nwas really cathartic for me,"},{"time":304245,"text":"because I realized\nthat this famous scientist"},{"time":307802,"text":"had documented\nand scientifically validated"},{"time":310986,"text":"something that we've seen happen\nfor the last 30 years:"},{"time":314401,"text":"that we could take people who had the fear\nthat they weren't creative,"},{"time":318214,"text":"and we could take them\nthrough a series of steps,"},{"time":320964,"text":"kind of like a series of small successes,"},{"time":324384,"text":"and they turn fear into familiarity."},{"time":328315,"text":"And they surprise themselves."},{"time":329814,"text":"That transformation is amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331841,"text":"We see it at the d.school all the time."},{"time":334261,"text":"People from all different\nkinds of disciplines,"},{"time":336991,"text":"they think of themselves\nas only analytical."},{"time":339506,"text":"And they come in and they go\nthrough the process, our process,"},{"time":343034,"text":"they build confidence and now\nthey think of themselves differently."},{"time":346240,"text":"And they're totally emotionally excited\nabout the fact that they walk around"},{"time":351329,"text":"thinking of themselves\nas a creative person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355566,"text":"So I thought one\nof the things I'd do today"},{"time":357646,"text":"is take you through and show you\nwhat this journey looks like."},{"time":361478,"text":"To me, that journey looks like Doug Dietz."},{"time":368226,"text":"Doug Dietz is a technical person."},{"time":370164,"text":"He designs large\nmedical imaging equipment."},{"time":374432,"text":"He's worked for GE, and he's had\na fantastic career."},{"time":378242,"text":"But at one point,\nhe had a moment of crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381066,"text":"He was in the hospital looking\nat one of his MRI machines in use,"},{"time":385163,"text":"when he saw a young family,\nand this little girl."},{"time":388787,"text":"And that little girl was crying\nand was terrified."},{"time":392263,"text":"And Doug was really disappointed to learn"},{"time":395642,"text":"that nearly 80 percent\nof the pediatric patients in this hospital"},{"time":399521,"text":"had to be sedated in order\nto deal with his MRI machine."},{"time":405065,"text":"And this was really disappointing to Doug,"},{"time":407168,"text":"because before this time,\nhe was proud of what he did."},{"time":409845,"text":"He was saving lives with this machine."},{"time":412437,"text":"But it really hurt him to see the fear\nthat this machine caused in kids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417438,"text":"About that time, he was at the d.school\nat Stanford taking classes."},{"time":421922,"text":"He was learning about our process,\nabout design thinking, about empathy,"},{"time":426597,"text":"about iterative prototyping."},{"time":428446,"text":"And he would take this new knowledge\nand do something quite extraordinary."},{"time":433159,"text":"He would redesign the entire experience"},{"time":436920,"text":"of being scanned."},{"time":438560,"text":"And this is what he came up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440183,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":441226,"text":"He turned it into\nan adventure for the kids."},{"time":443823,"text":"He painted the walls\nand he painted the machine,"},{"time":446105,"text":"and he got the operators retrained\nby people who know kids,"},{"time":448908,"text":"like children's museum people."},{"time":451442,"text":"And now when the kid comes,\nit's an experience."},{"time":455164,"text":"And they talk to them about the noise\nand the movement of the ship."},{"time":458794,"text":"And when they come, they say,"},{"time":460215,"text":"\"OK, you're going to go\ninto the pirate ship,"},{"time":462366,"text":"but be very still, because we don't want\nthe pirates to find you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":467314,"text":"And the results were super dramatic:"},{"time":470974,"text":"from something like 80 percent\nof the kids needing to be sedated,"},{"time":474148,"text":"to something like 10 percent\nof the kids needing to be sedated."},{"time":478426,"text":"And the hospital and GE were happy, too,"},{"time":480489,"text":"because you didn't have to call\nthe anesthesiologist all the time,"},{"time":483672,"text":"and they could put more kids\nthrough the machine in a day."},{"time":486504,"text":"So the quantitative results were great."},{"time":488435,"text":"But Doug's results that he cared about\nwere much more qualitative."},{"time":492463,"text":"He was with one of the mothers"},{"time":494213,"text":"waiting for her child\nto come out of the scan."},{"time":496547,"text":"And when the little girl\ncame out of her scan,"},{"time":498937,"text":"she ran up to her mother and said,"},{"time":500857,"text":"\"Mommy, can we come back tomorrow?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":502821,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":506046,"text":"And so, I've heard Doug tell\nthe story many times"},{"time":509491,"text":"of his personal transformation"},{"time":511801,"text":"and the breakthrough design\nthat happened from it,"},{"time":515171,"text":"but I've never really seen him\ntell the story of the little girl"},{"time":518306,"text":"without a tear in his eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520055,"text":"Doug's story takes place in a hospital."},{"time":523021,"text":"I know a thing or two about hospitals."},{"time":526470,"text":"A few years ago, I felt a lump\non the side of my neck."},{"time":531211,"text":"It was my turn in the MRI machine."},{"time":533964,"text":"It was cancer, it was the bad kind."},{"time":536948,"text":"I was told I had a 40 percent\nchance of survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540903,"text":"So while you're sitting\naround with the other patients,"},{"time":543833,"text":"in your pajamas,"},{"time":545081,"text":"and everybody's pale and thin --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":547133,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":548173,"text":"you know? -- and you're waiting\nfor your turn to get the gamma rays,"},{"time":551462,"text":"you think of a lot of things."},{"time":553138,"text":"Mostly, you think about:\nAm I going to survive?"},{"time":556381,"text":"And I thought a lot about:"},{"time":557673,"text":"What was my daughter's life\ngoing to be like without me?"},{"time":562496,"text":"But you think about other things."},{"time":564938,"text":"I thought a lot about:\nWhat was I put on Earth to do?"},{"time":567948,"text":"What was my calling? What should I do?"},{"time":571363,"text":"I was lucky because I had lots of options."},{"time":573435,"text":"We'd been working in health and wellness,"},{"time":575418,"text":"and K-12, and the developing world."},{"time":577540,"text":"so there were lots of projects\nthat I could work on."},{"time":580612,"text":"But then I decided\nand committed at this point,"},{"time":582954,"text":"to the thing I most wanted to do,"},{"time":586234,"text":"which was to help as many\npeople as possible"},{"time":589949,"text":"regain the creative confidence\nthey lost along their way."},{"time":593822,"text":"And if I was going to survive,\nthat's what I wanted to do."},{"time":596670,"text":"I survived, just so you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598155,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":600250,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":606983,"text":"I really believe that when people\ngain this confidence --"},{"time":610912,"text":"and we see it all the time\nat the d.school and at IDEO --"},{"time":613937,"text":"that they actually start\nworking on the things"},{"time":616759,"text":"that are really important in their lives."},{"time":618770,"text":"We see people quit what they're doing\nand go in new directions."},{"time":622505,"text":"We see them come up with more\ninteresting -- and just more -- ideas,"},{"time":628978,"text":"so they can choose from better ideas."},{"time":631905,"text":"And they just make better decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634498,"text":"I know at TED, you're supposed to have\na change-the-world kind of thing,"},{"time":638015,"text":"isn't that -- everybody has\na change-the-world thing?"},{"time":640739,"text":"If there is one for me, this is it,\nto help this happen."},{"time":643890,"text":"So I hope you'll join me on my quest,"},{"time":646654,"text":"you as, kind of, thought leaders."},{"time":648288,"text":"It would be really great if you didn't let\npeople divide the world"},{"time":652553,"text":"into the creatives and the non-creatives,\nlike it's some God-given thing,"},{"time":656539,"text":"and to have people realize\nthat they're naturally creative,"},{"time":661049,"text":"and that those natural people\nshould let their ideas fly;"},{"time":665665,"text":"that they should achieve\nwhat Bandura calls self-efficacy,"},{"time":669865,"text":"that you can do what you set out to do,"},{"time":673152,"text":"and that you can reach a place\nof creative confidence"},{"time":676864,"text":"and touch the snake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678572,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679748,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}